The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 July is 45,969 (5,320.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 July, there were 1,334 new confirmed cases (154.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 June, there were 720 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 85% (614 extra cases).
